<CppDocsLayout title="C++ Overview" description="A structured collection of notes for learning modern C++ from setup through core language concepts." current="overview" {headings} next={{ title:'Installing C++', href:'/programming-languages/cpp/installation/' }}>
  <section id="about-cpp"><h2>About C++</h2><p>C++ is a compiled, statically typed programming language designed for performance, control, and abstraction. It is widely used in systems software, game engines, embedded applications, desktop software, and performance-sensitive services.</p><p>These notes focus on modern C++ practices while explaining the lower-level behavior that makes the language powerful.</p></section>
  <section id="what-you-will-learn"><h2>What you will learn</h2><ul><li>Installing and configuring a C++ compiler.</li><li>Reading input and displaying output.</li><li>Variables, types, operators, and control flow.</li><li>Functions, classes, memory, and resource ownership.</li><li>The C++ standard library and modern language features.</li></ul></section>
  <section id="how-to-use"><h2>How to use these notes</h2><p>Read the notes in sidebar order when learning C++ for the first time. Each page builds on concepts introduced earlier. If you already know the fundamentals, use the sidebar and the table of contents to jump directly to a topic.</p><div class="callout"><p>Start with <strong>Installation</strong> to configure the toolchain used by the examples.</p></div></section>
